# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` (for development) and set the values accordingly.
For production on Railway, set these via Railway dashboard â†’ Variables.

## Core Application
NODE_ENV=development
APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

## Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/immigration_db

## Redis (for queue jobs)
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

## Authentication
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-generate-with-openssl-rand-base64-32

## CORS & Host (Railway only: set to your Railway domain)
# Example: https://myapp-production-xxxx.up.railway.app
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5000

## Email/SMTP (choose one provider)

### Option A: SendGrid
SENDGRID_API_KEY=

### Option B: Generic SMTP
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
SMTP_FROM=noreply@immigrationai.com

## Payments (Stripe)
# In production set a live or test secret key in Railway / host env: STRIPE_SECRET_KEY
# Example (test): STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_4eC39HqLyjWDarjtT1zdp7dc
# If STRIPE_SECRET_KEY is missing in development the server will use a lightweight mock to allow local testing.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_test_
STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_

## AI/LLM Configuration (choose one)

### Option A: Hugging Face Inference API
HUGGINGFACE_API_TOKEN=hf_
HF_MODEL=OpenAssistant/replit-1b-instruct

### Option B: Self-hosted Inference Server
HF_INFERENCE_URL=http://localhost:8080
HUGGINGFACE_API_TOKEN=

### Option C: OpenAI (paid)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

## AWS S3 (optional, for file storage)
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_S3_BUCKET=

## Development Tools
DEBUG=immigrationai:*
LOG_LEVEL=debug

## Port
PORT=3000
